Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2772/75 of 29 October 1975 on marketing standards for eggs (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 3494/86 (2), and in particular Articles 1, 6 and 9 thereof,
Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 95/69 (3), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 3759/85 (4), contains the provisions required for the implementation of certain marketing standards for hen eggs in shell;
Whereas these provisions should be adapted in accordance with the recent amendments of Regulation (EEC) No 2772/75 as regards the exclusion of incubated eggs from use for food purposes;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Poultrymeat and Eggs,

main_body:
Regulation (EEC) No 95/69 is hereby amended as follows:
1. Article 6 (2) (c) is deleted;
2. Article 9 is deleted.
